snippet.textDisplay:
Here’s a toast to all of the morbidly obese alcoholics who don’t give a darn about their health, and are annoyed that anyone would remind them that their slothful lifestyle is racing them headlong toward an early grave.

I assume that most SJWs and radical feminists are alcoholics, anyway, so this was a brilliant ad to capture that particular segment of the market. 😛

The people who are shaming Peloton for their commercial are probably not the kind to exercise, anyway, so I doubt that Peloton is losing customers. Any publicity is good publicity.

Did it ever occur to all the lazy haters out there that the the point of the commercial was that the woman probably asked her husband for an exercise bike, and he bought her the deluxe model? Otherwise, why would she be happy? I assume that her hobby is bike riding (believe it or not, many people actually LIKE to exercise, unlike the morbidly obese haters).

Besides, it is obvious that skinny people exercise; that is why they are (still) skinny. And everyone NEEDS exercise no matter what their body shape or fitness level. Being a couch potato lowers your life expectancy as much as smoking, no matter how skinny you are.
